20solo%20401(k).%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ENow%2C%20he's%20increasing%20his%20small-cap%20exposure%20with%20the%20NEOS%20Russell%202000%20High%20Income%20ETF.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EAustin%20Hankwitz%20has%20always%20loved%20analyzing%20stocks.%20In%202020%2C%20he%20began%20posting%20TikTok%20videos%20on%20the%20side%2C%20sharing%20his%20insights%20on%20stocks%20while%20juggling%20his%20job%20as%20a%20financial%20analyst%20for%20a%20healthcare%20company%2C%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHis%20ability%20to%20explain%20investing%20concepts%20and%20break%20down%20stock%20picks%20helped%20his%20side%20gig%20amass%20over%20700%2C000%20followers.%20His%20successful%20content%20pushed%20him%20to%20become%20a%20full-time%20personal%20finance%20content%20creator.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20December%202022%2C%20he%20wanted%20to%20take%20his%20content%20one%20step%20further%20by%20creating%20an%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance-creator-investment-portfolio-plan-to-reach-millions-2023-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20investing%20challenge%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20others%20could%20track%20and%20follow.%20Simply%20put%2C%20it%20was%20to%20build%20a%20portfolio%20worth%20%242%20million%20in%20eight%20to%2015%20years.%20His%20ultimate%20goal%20by%20the%20end%20of%20it%20was%20to%20have%20enough%20dividend-paying%20stocks%20that%20could%20pay%20out%20%2480%2C000%20to%20%2490%2C000%20annually.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%2028-year-old%20began%20experimenting%20with%20different%20types%20of%20securities%20to%20reach%20his%20goal.%20Being%20young%20meant%20that%20he%20still%20had%20many%20years%20to%20retire.%20This%20meant%20he%20could%20afford%20to%20ride%20out%20market%20volatility%20or%20make%20a%20few%20mistakes%20here%20and%20there%20while%20his%20followers%20took%20cues%20from%20his%20experiences.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20the%20challenge%2C%20he%20uses%20a%20regular%20brokerage%20account%20and%20a%20retirement%20account.%20In%20the%20brokerage%2C%20he%20can%20contribute%20as%20much%20as%20he%20wants.%20There%2C%20he%20holds%20dividend%20stocks%2C%20technology%20stocks%2C%20a%20few%20ETFs%2C%20and%20the%20S%26amp%3BP%20500.%20In%20the%20retirement%20portion%2C%20he%20has%20a%20self-employed%20or%20solo%20401(k)%20that%20has%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Finvesting%2Fwhat-is-roth-ira%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ERoth%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20an%20annual%20contribution%20limit%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Finvesting%2F401k-contribution-limits%23%3A~%3Atext%3DA%2520401(k)%2520is%2520a%2Cmust%2520withdraw%2520the%2520extra%2520funds.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%2423%2C000%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20an%20after-tax%20account%20with%20no%20contribution%20limit%20where%20he%20invests%20in%20Vanguard%20indexes%20and%20individual%20stocks.%20He%20also%20has%20added%20some%20bitcoin.%20His%20account%20values%20now%20sit%20at%20over%20%24391%2C000%2C%20according%20to%20records%20of%20his%20brokerages%20viewed%20by%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22ce8b7c64-af74-4219-a294-b205196628ce%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EThis%20year's%20options%20ETF%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EHankwitz%20enjoys%20hunting%20for%20ETFs%20with%20a%20unique%20edge%20over%20their%20peers.%20He%20previously%20began%20investing%20in%20the%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftax-efficient-fund-with-high-yield-build-million-dollar-portfolio-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20NEOS%20Nasdaq-100%20High%20Income%20ETF%3C%2Fa%3E%20(QQQI)%20because%20it%20exposed%20him%20to%20stocks%20within%20the%20Nasdaq%20100%20while%20trading%20call%20options%20on%20the%20index.%20The%20second%20part%20allows%20the%20ETF%20to%20provide%20monthly%20payouts%20that%20equal%20an%20annual%20yield%20of%2014.96%25%20at%20a%200.68%25%20expense%20ratio.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20also%20began%20investing%20in%20a%20similar%20ETF%20for%20the%20S%26amp%3BP%20500%20called%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftax-efficient-fund-with-high-yield-build-million-dollar-portfolio-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ENEOS%20S%26amp%3BP%20500%20High%20Income%20ETF%3C%2Fa%3E%20(SPYI).%20It%20leverages%20the%20same%20options%20strategy%20for%20500%20of%20the%20biggest%20US%20companies.%20It%20distributes%20a%20yield%20monthly%20for%20a%20total%20annual%20yield%20of%2012.34%25%20at%20a%200.68%25%20expense%20ratio.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBoth%20ETFs%20were%20timely%20because%20they%20allowed%20Hankwitz%20to%20gain%20exposure%20to%20large-cap%20technology%20stocks%2C%20which%20led%20to%20market%20gains%20in%202023%20and%20into%202024.%20But%20as%20we%20near%20the%20end%20of%20the%20year%2C%20the%20Federal%20Reserve%20is%20expected%20to%20cut%20rates%2C%20which%20could%20cause%20a%20rotation%20of%20equities.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20debt%20becomes%20cheaper%2C%20small-cap%20stocks%20that%20had%20been%20largely%20left%20behind%20are%20expected%20to%20gain%20from%20an%20easing%20economic%20environment.%20The%20Russell%202000%20saw%20early%20signs%20of%20that%20as%20the%20small-cap%20index%20rallied%20in%20July%2C%20initially%20sparked%20by%20weaker-than-expected%20CPI%20data%2C%20according%20to%20a%20Bank%20of%20America%20note%20from%20August%205.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20the%20index%20reversed%20shortly%20after%20as%20a%20slew%20of%20negative%20economic%20data%20began%20to%20roll%20in%2C%20including%20higher-than-anticipated%20unemployment%20and%20a%20slowing%20manufacturing%20sector.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20markets%20anticipate%20a%20high%20probability%20of%20the%20first%20rate%20cut%20this%20year%20in%20September%20which%20could%20put%20small%20caps%20back%20in%20favor.%20With%20that%20in%20mind%2C%20Hankwitz%20began%20increasing%20his%20exposure%20to%20small%20caps.%20But%20instead%20of%20buying%20ETFs%20that%20just%20track%20the%20Russell%202000%2C%20he%20invested%20in%20one%20with%20the%20same%20structure%20as%20the%20SPYI%20and%20QQQI%20from%20the%20same%20firm%3A%20the%20%3Cstrong%3ENEOS%20Russell%202000%20High%20Income%20ETF%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20(IWMI).%20The%20fund%20is%20actively%20managed%20with%20exposure%20to%20the%20Russell%202000%20while%20leveraging%20options%20to%20take%20advantage%20of%20tax%20loss%20harvesting.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20ETF%20sells%20and%20purchases%20options%20on%20the%20Russell%202000%20in%20an%20attempt%20to%20capture%20the%20index's%20upside.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20pays%20a%20monthly%20yield%20for%20a%20total%20annual%20yield%20of%2014.03%25%20with%20a%20.68%25%20expense%20ratio.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20bet%20has%20two%20advantages.%20The%20first%20is%20to%20ride%20the%20potential%20upside%20of%20small-cap%20gains%20he's%20expecting.%20The%20second%20is%20to%20earn%20a%20steady%20monthly%20payout%20while%20he%20waits%20for%20the%20small-cap%20rally%20to%20play%20out.%20This%20eases%20tensions%20around%20investing%20to%20try%20to%20time%20market%20rotations.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fetf-paying-distribution-yield-with-tax-advantages-personal-finance-creator-2024-8%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1723886521000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66bfb50db4912df3ae1c737f%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fetf-paying-distribution-yield-with-tax-advantages-personal-finance-creator-2024-8%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Hankwitz%20is%20building%20a%20retirement%20portfolio%20worth%20%242%20million%20with%20investments%20that%20expedite%20returns.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22lmaidan%40businessinsider.com%20(Laila%20Maidan)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fetf-paying-distribution-yield-with-tax-advantages-personal-finance-creator-2024-8%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%