elf-to-work-limits-jobs-politics-google-firings-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epolitical%20talk%20at%20work%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20a%20problem%20because%20mudslinging%20on%20the%20job%20can%20make%20it%20harder%20for%20coworkers%20to%20get%20along%20and%20can%20cut%20into%20how%20well%20teams%20perform.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20answer%2C%20difficult%20as%20it%20might%20be%2C%20is%20to%20leave%20politics%20at%20the%20cubicle's%20edge.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJoe%20Galvin%2C%20chief%20research%20officer%20at%20the%20executive-coaching%20firm%20Vistage%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20managers%20must%20look%20out%20for%20political%20speech%20at%20work%20just%20as%20they%20would%20hate%20speech%20or%20discrimination.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20goal%2C%20he%20said%2C%20is%20to%20make%20clear%20to%20employees%20that%20talking%20politics%20at%20work%20%E2%80%94%20beyond%20policy%20discussions%20that%20might%20affect%20the%20business%20%E2%80%94%20isn't%20worth%20the%20cost.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20it's%20connected%20to%20your%20business%2C%20it's%20appropriate%20to%20discuss%20it%20in%20the%20context%20of%20the%20business.%20Otherwise%2C%20it%20doesn't%20belong%20in%20the%20workplace%2C%26quot%3B%20Galvin%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20in%20a%20time%20when%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbring-your-whole-self-to-work-doesnt-promote-inclusion-experts-say-2021-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebring%20your%20whole%20self%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20work%20trope%20persists%2C%20leaving%20politics%20outside%20the%20job%20can%20be%20hard.%20In%20a%20recent%20Indeed%20survey%2C%20about%20a%20third%20of%20respondents%20said%20they%20openly%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.indeed.com%2Fcareer-advice%2Fnews%2Fpolitical-differences-workplace%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ediscussed%20politics%20at%20work%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20behavior%20wasn't%20a%20winner%20for%20most%20workers.%20Fifty-four%20percent%20of%20those%20surveyed%20reported%20being%20uncomfortable%20when%20political%20talk%20worked%20its%20way%20into%20meetings.%20The%20online%20survey%2C%20conducted%20by%20Harris%20Poll%2C%20involved%20about%201%2C100%20working%20adults%20in%20the%20US%20and%20took%20place%20from%20late%20July%20to%20early%20August.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22b64b7af8-8be6-4cf4-ac7e-ca9fdbf7cf3f%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EMaking%20teams%20work%20better%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EFinding%20a%20way%20to%20ditch%20politics%20during%20business%20hours%20can%20benefit%20workers%20by%20giving%20them%20a%20break%20from%20exhausting%20conversations.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20important%20because%20having%20political%20conversations%20at%20work%20typically%20leads%20people%20to%20feel%20depleted%2C%20according%20to%20Jake%20Telkamp%2C%20an%20assistant%20professor%20at%20the%20Hull%20College%20of%20Business%20at%20Augusta%20University%20in%20Georgia.%20And%20when%20workers%20feel%20drained%2C%20they%20might%20be%20less%20inclined%20to%20help%20their%20colleagues%2C%20he%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20research%20he's%20conducted%20with%20colleagues%2C%20Telkamp%20found%20that%20teams%20comprised%20of%20people%20with%20diverse%20political%20viewpoints%20tend%20to%20have%20more%20disputes%2C%20which%20in%20turn%20makes%20them%20less%20effective.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThat%20had%20a%20really%20bad%20impact%20down%20the%20road%20on%20team%20performance%2C%20rated%20by%20their%20leader%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%2C%20Telkamp%20said%2C%20there%20is%20a%20way%20to%20guard%20against%20this%20pernicious%20drag%20on%20team%20performance%3A%20Fostering%20a%20culture%20of%20respect.%20He%20said%20workers%20benefit%20when%20they%20believe%20that%20people%20with%20differing%20views%20will%20be%20treated%20the%20same.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThat's%20the%20buffering%20effect%2C%26quot%3B%20Telkamp%20said.%20%26quot%3BWe%20can%20reduce%20those%20interpersonal%20issues%20that%20have%20such%20a%20negative%20impact.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2203c6259d-e20a-4a0b-ac8a-dcb99f4ec179%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EIt's%20not%20always%20easy%20to%20say%20what's%20political%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EPolitical%20chatter%20at%20work%20isn't%20a%20concern%20just%20because%20it%20can%20lead%20to%20clashes%20among%20coworkers.%20It%20can%20also%20be%20difficult%20for%20employers%20to%20cordon%20off.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDomenique%20Camacho%20Moran%2C%20an%20employment%20attorney%20with%20the%20firm%20Farrell%20Fritz%20in%20New%20York%2C%20told%20BI%20that%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20private%20employers%2C%20workers%20generally%20don't%20have%20a%20right%20to%20broadcast%20their%20political%20views%20on%20the%20job.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20said%20most%20employers%20don't%20tend%20to%20tell%20workers%20what%20they%20can%20talk%20about.%20Instead%2C%20private%20employers%20more%20often%20focus%20on%20what's%20off-limits.%20That%20often%20includes%20language%20that%20would%20harass%20colleagues%20based%20on%20a%20list%20of%20protected%20categories%20like%20race%20or%20religion.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECamacho%20Moran%20said%20employers%20can%20prohibit%20political%20conversation%2C%20but%20one%20risk%20is%20inconsistency%20in%20enforcement.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBesides%2C%20she%20said%2C%20determining%20what%20is%20political%20speech%20can%20be%20difficult.%20Camacho%20Moran%20pointed%20to%20a%20recent%20dustup%20over%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fapnews.com%2Farticle%2Folympics-2024-opening-ceremony-last-supper-criticism-9dd5fc5f1849ce9b0720fa997f38ed27%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eopening%20ceremony%20at%20the%20Olympics%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Some%20religious%20conservatives%20decried%20the%20performance%20for%20making%20what%20they%20saw%20as%20disrespectful%20allusions%20to%20Leonardo%20da%20Vinci's%20%26quot%3BThe%20Last%20Supper.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAm%20I%20allowed%20to%20talk%20about%20the%20Olympics%2C%20or%20is%20that%20political%20speech%3F%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSo%2C%20it's%20a%20slippery%20slope%20for%20an%20employer%20to%20start%20going%20down%20the%20road%20of%20no%20political%20speech%2C%26quot%3B%20Camacho%20Moran%20said.%20Instead%2C%20she%20said%2C%20employers%20can%20enforce%20%26quot%3Breasonable%20standards%26quot%3B%20that%20might%20prohibit%20people%20from%20having%20arguments%20or%20distracting%20colleagues.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20we%20have%20employers%20who%20are%20more%20focused%20on%20conduct%2C%20not%20content%2C%20they%20are%20better%20served%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStomping%20out%20political%20brushfires%20at%20work%20might%20also%20help%20employers%20hang%20onto%20their%20people.%20In%20the%20Indeed%20survey%2C%20about%20a%20quarter%20of%20workers%20%E2%80%94%20and%20about%20four%20in%2010%20Gen%20Zers%20and%20millennials%20%E2%80%94%20said%20they%20would%20think%20about%20quitting%20over%20political%20discord%20on%20the%20job.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETelkamp%2C%20the%20Augusta%20University%20researcher%2C%20said%20that%20another%20reason%20trading%20political%20jabs%20at%20work%20is%20a%20bad%20idea%20is%20because%20doing%20so%20is%20unlikely%20to%20change%20anyone's%20mind.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInstead%2C%20he%20said%2C%20leaders%20and%20workers%20should%20focus%20on%20making%20people%20feel%20like%20they're%20valued%20regardless%20of%20their%20background.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20there%20was%20a%20high%20level%20of%20that%2C%20it%20reduced%20that%20negative%20effect%20of%20having%20liberals%20and%20conservatives%20on%20a%20team%20together%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjob-politics-talking-discussions-work-rules-election-hr-trump-harris-2024-8%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1723885922000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F669f59fbfb2b6bedb0597599%