ial%20primary%20debate%2C%20when%20Gabbard%20eviscerated%20Harris%20in%20a%20memorable%20onstage%20encounter.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKaroline%20Leavitt%2C%20a%20spokeswoman%20for%20Trump%2C%20confirmed%20Gabbard's%20involvement%20in%20an%20email%2C%20NYT%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELeavitt%20said%20the%20former%20president%20has%20%26quot%3Bproven%20to%20be%20one%20of%20the%20best%20debaters%20in%20political%20history%20as%20evidenced%20by%20his%20knockout%20blow%20to%20Joe%20Biden.%20He%20does%20not%20need%20traditional%20debate%20prep%20but%20will%20continue%20to%20meet%20with%20respected%20policy%20advisers%20and%20effective%20communicators%20like%20Tulsi%20Gabbard%2C%20who%20successfully%20dominated%20Kamala%20Harris%20on%20the%20debate%20stage%20in%202020.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThough%20Trump%20says%20he%20%26quot%3Bdoesn't%20need%20to%26quot%3B%20prepare%20for%20debates%2C%20the%20former%20President%20has%20spent%20more%20time%20this%20year%20practicing%20for%20debates%20than%20he%20did%20in%20either%202016%20or%202020%2C%20the%20New%20York%20Times%20reported%20citing%20advisers%20who%20have%20worked%20with%20him.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20still%20doesn't%20do%20traditional%20debate%20prep.%20Nobody%20played%20Mr.%20Biden%20in%20his%20sessions%20ahead%20of%20their%20CNN%20debate%20on%20June%2027.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAhead%20of%20his%20CNN%20debate%20with%20Biden%20in%20June%2C%20Trump%20sat%20with%20advisers%20for%20blocks%20of%20time%20or%20informally%20on%20plane%20trips%20and%20discussed%20potential%20topics%20and%20lines%20of%20questioning.%20In%20more%20formal%20sessions%20at%20Mar-a-Lago%2C%20aides%20have%20sat%20in%20chairs%20opposite%20him%2C%20playing%20the%20role%20of%20moderators.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERepresentative%20Matt%20Gaetz%20of%20Florida%20asked%20especially%20combative%20questions%2C%20according%20to%20a%20person%20who%20was%20in%20the%20room.%20Other%20lawmakers%2C%20including%20his%20eventual%20running%20mate%2C%20Senator%20JD%20Va