20at%20the%20gym%20before%20heading%20to%20bed.%20The%20actor%20added%20he%20has%20only%20one%20meal%20a%20day%20and%20it%20has%20nothing%20to%20do%20with%20intermittent%20fasting...%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22TOI%20Entertainment%20Desk%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fentertainment%2Fhindi%2Fbollywood%2Fnews%2Fshah-rukh-khans-daily-routine-fitness-secret-revealed-i-go-to-sleep-at-5am-eat-one-meal-a-day%2Farticleshow%2F112581188.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Sunita%20Williams%20Stuck%20In%20Space%3A%20What%206%20Months%20Can%20Do%20To%20Perception%20Of%20Time%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3ETwo%20astronauts%20marooned%20in%20space%20may%20sound%20like%20the%20plot%20of%20a%20Hollywood%20blockbuster%2C%20but%20for%20two%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nasa.gov%2F%5C%22%3ENASA%3C%2Fa%3E%20crew%20members%2C%20it%20is%20now%20a%20reality.%20Commander%20Barry%20Wilmore%20and%20pilot%20Sunita%20Williams%20are%20currently%20in%20limbo%20on%20the%20International%20Space%20Station%20(ISS).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThey%20arrived%20in%20the%20Boeing%20Starliner%20spacecraft%20%E2%80%93%20the%20first%20test%20of%20the%20spaceship%20with%20astronauts.%20Wilmore%20and%20Williams%20were%20supposed%20to%20stay%20on%20the%20ISS%20for%20around%20eight%20days%20and%20return%20on%20the%20same%20spacecraft.%20But%20there%20is%20now%20debate%20about%20the%20safety%20of%20Starliner%20after%20it%20experienced%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Farticles%2Fc6pp29gdwe6o%5C%22%3Ehelium%20leaks%20and%20thruster%20problems%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20its%20way%20to%20the%20ISS.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20coming%20days%2C%20NASA%20and%20Boeing%20may%20decide%20to%20clear%20Starliner%20to%20carry%20the%20astronauts%20back%20to%20Earth.%20This%20means%20their%20stay%20might%20not%20last%20too%20much%20longer.%20But%20if%20officials%20decide%20against%20Starliner%2C%20the%20astronauts%20face%20waiting%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nasa.gov%2Fnews-release%2Fupdate-nasa-boeing-to-stream-flight-test-mission-briefing-on-nasa%2F%5C%22%3Eadditional%20six%20months%20in%20orbit%3C%2Fa%3E%20before%20returning.%20So%20how%20do%20astronauts%20cope%20with%20a%20potential%20six-month%20wait%20for%20a%20lift%20home%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sciencedirect.com%2Fscience%2Farticle%2Fabs%2Fpii%2F0022249685900203%5C%22%3EWaiting%20for%20things%20is%20difficult%3C%2Fa%3E%20at%20the%20best%20of%20times.%20Under%20normal%20circumstances%2C%20it%20is%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fjournals.sagepub.com%2Fdoi%2Ffull%2F10.1177%2F2043808718778982%5C%22%3Efrustrating%2C%20stressful%20and%20anxiety-provoking%3C%2Fa%3E.%20But%20in%20extreme%20situations%2C%20with%20high%20stakes%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fonlinelibrary.wiley.com%2Fdoi%2Ffull%2F10.1111%2Fj.1365-2648.2011.05638.x%3Fcasa_token%3DjC_hT4wqbuIAAAAA%253AGTrJPmd496aDTdirdwYi7CvLK8Q1g_oR-Em2E3EpDP0AwRCs2ko13Jpqui15BlkPiAx7MMRqA0MC%5C%22%3Ewaiting%20can%20be%20purgatory%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPart%20of%20the%20reason%20that%20waiting%20is%20difficult%20is%20that%20it%20distorts%20our%20sense%20of%20time.%20Think%20of%20last%20time%20you%20were%20waiting%20for%20a%20delayed%20train%2C%20test%20results%20or%20a%20text%20from%20a%20potential%20new%20partner.%20Did%20it%20fly%20by%20or%20drag%3F%20For%20most%20people%2C%20time%20spent%20waiting%20crawls%20at%20a%20glacial%20pace.%20As%20a%20result%2C%20delays%20and%20periods%20of%20anticipation%20often%20feel%20much%20longer%20than%20they%20actually%20are.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWaiting%20slows%20our%20perception%20of%20time%2C%20because%20it%20changes%20the%20amount%20of%20time%20that%20we%20spend%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.jstor.org%2Fstable%2F23324610%3Fcasa_token%3DKmtJWWmtHwQAAAAA%253AN_CUdtNakK46j4ItZaH_f__QcIGOjMnasX1NeMTRFH5YPpcmYx1JpigTfTb1bPYi5Fcus-IhtzDX0Jsz3xpqZRMDUxg0RWYhSr87V-zXz_pqS0zM%26seq%3D2%5C%22%3Ethinking%20about%20time%3C%2Fa%3E.%20During%20normal%20daily%20life%20we%20often%20ignore%20time%3B%20our%20brains%20have%20a%20limited%20capacity.%20If%20time%20isn't%20important%2C%20we%20simply%20don't%20think%20about%20it%2C%20and%20this%20helps%20it%20to%20pass%20quickly.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20we%20are%20waiting%2C%20our%20desire%20to%20know%20when%20the%20wait%20is%20over%20increases%20how%20much%20we%20think%20about%20time.%20This%20%E2%80%9Cclock%20watching%E2%80%9D%20can%20make%20the%20minutes%20and%20hours%20feel%20like%20they%20are%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdoi.org%2F10.1016%2F0278-2626(90)90026-K%5C%22%3Epassing%20at%20a%20snail's%20pace%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Stress%2C%20discomfort%20and%20pain%20exacerbate%20this%20effect%2C%20meaning%20that%20waiting%20in%20difficult%20situations%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdoi.org%2F10.1002%2Fejp.2211%5C%22%3Ecan%20seem%20even%20longer%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22Starliner%20in%20orbit.%5C%22%20sizes%3D%5C%22(min-width%3A%201466px)%20754px%2C%20(max-width%3A%20599px)%20100vw%2C%20(min-width%3A%20600px)%20600px%2C%20237px%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fimages.theconversation.com%2Ffiles%2F612803%2Foriginal%2Ffile-20240811-19-xa3g2p.jpg%3Fixlib%3Drb-4.1.0%26amp%3Bq%3D45%26amp%3Bauto%3Dformat%26amp%3Bw%3D600%26amp%3Bh%3D400%26amp%3Bfit%3Dcrop%26amp%3Bdpr%3D1%20600w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fimages.theconversation.com%2Ffiles%2F612803%2Foriginal%2Ffile-20240811-19-xa3g2p.jpg%3Fixlib%3Drb-4.1.0%26amp%3Bq%3D30%26amp%3Bauto%3Dformat%26amp%3Bw%3D600%26amp%3Bh%3D400%26amp%3Bfit%3Dcrop%26amp%3Bdpr%3D2%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fimages.theconversation.com%2Ffiles%2F612803%2Foriginal%2Ffile-20240811-19-xa3g2p.jpg%3Fixlib%3Drb-4.1.0%26amp%3Bq%3D15%26amp%3Bauto%3Dformat%26amp%3Bw%3D600%26amp%3Bh%3D400%26amp%3Bfit%3Dcrop%26amp%3Bdpr%3D3%201800w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fimages.theconversation.com%2Ffiles%2F612803%2Foriginal%2Ffile-20240811-19-xa3g2p.jpg%3Fixlib%3Drb-4.1.0%26amp%3Bq%3D45%26amp%3Bauto%3Dformat%26amp%3Bw%3D754%26amp%3Bh%3D503%26amp%3Bfit%3Dcrop%26amp%3Bdpr%3D1%20754w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fimages.theconversation.com%2Ffiles%2F612803%2Foriginal%2Ffile-20240811-19-xa3g2p.jpg%3Fixlib%3Drb-4.1.0%26amp%3Bq%3D30%26amp%3Bauto%3Dformat%26amp%3Bw%3D754%26amp%3Bh%3D503%26amp%3Bfit%3Dcrop%26amp%3Bdpr%3D2%201508w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fimages.theconversation.com%2Ffiles%2F612803%2Foriginal%2Ffile-20240811-19-xa3g2p.jpg%3Fixlib%3Drb-4.1.0%26amp%3Bq%3D15%26amp%3Bauto%3Dformat%26amp%3Bw%3D754%26amp%3Bh%3D503%26amp%3Bfit%3Dcrop%26amp%3Bdpr%3D3%202262w%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fimages.theconversation.com%2Ffiles%2F612803%2Foriginal%2Ffile-20240811-19-xa3g2p.jpg%3Fixlib%3Drb-4.1.0%26q%3D45%26auto%3Dformat%26w%3D754%26fit%3Dclip%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cspan%3EStarliner%20in%20orbit.%3C%2Fspan%3E%20%3Cspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nasa.gov%2Fnews-release%2Fupdate-nasa-boeing-to-stream-flight-test-mission-briefing-on-nasa%2F%5C%22%3ENasa%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ffigure%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWaiting%20also%20slows%20our%20perception%20of%20time%20because%20it%20what%20we%20do%20and%20how%20we%20feel.%20Normal%20life%20is%20busy%20and%20full%20of%20ever-changing%20activities%20and%20interactions.%20The%20sudden%20need%20to%20wait%20halts%20the%20flow%20of%20life%2C%20often%20leaving%20us%20with%20nothing%20else%20to%20do%2C%20thus%20increasing%20levels%20of%20boredom%20and%20frustration.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20general%2C%20time%20filled%20with%20activity%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdoi.org%2F10.1016%2F0278-2626(90)90026-K%5C%22%3Epasses%20more%20quickly%3C%2Fa%3E.%20We%20all%20got%20a%20taste%20of%20this%20during%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdoi.org%2F10.1371%2Fjournal.pone.0235871%5C%22%3ECOVID%20lockdowns%3C%2Fa%3E.%20When%20we%20were%20stuck%20inside%20unable%20to%20see%20friends%20and%20engage%20in%20normal%20daily%20activities%2C%20the%20loss%20of%20routine%20and%20distractions%20caused%20time%20to%20drag%20for%20many.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20the%20astronauts%20stuck%20on%20the%20ISS%2C%20anxiety%20about%20when%20they%20will%20return%2C%20limited%20opportunities%20for%20activities%20and%20fewer%20opportunities%20to%20contact%20friends%20and%20families%20combine%20to%20make%20their%20wait%20to%20return%20home%20feel%20significantly%20longer%20than%20six%20months%20%E2%80%93%20if%20it%20should%20come%20to%20that.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20as%20academics%20who%20research%20the%20effects%20of%20time%20on%20human%20psychology%20and%20biology%2C%20our%20ongoing%20work%20with%20crew%20members%20at%20research%20stations%20in%20Antarctica%20aims%20to%20shed%20light%20on%20whether%20waiting%20in%20extreme%20environments%20is%20different%20to%20waiting%20during%20normal%20daily%20life.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3EA%20year%20in%20Antarctica%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20being%20stuck%20for%20six%20months%20on%20the%20ISS%20may%20sound%20like%20many%20people's%20worst%20nightmare%2C%20it%20is%20not%20uncommon%20for%20scientists%20to%20spend%20long%20periods%20isolated%20and%20confined%20in%20extreme%20environments.%20Every%20year%2C%20organisations%20such%20as%20the%20Instituto%20Ant%C3%A1rtico%20Argentino%20(which%20uses%20the%20Belgrano%20II%20Antarctic%20station)%2C%20the%20French%20Polar%20Institute%20and%20the%20Italian%20Antarctic%20Programme%2C%20in%20cooperation%20with%20the%20European%20Space%20Agency%20(which%20all%20use%20Antarctica's%20Concordia%20station)%2C%20send%20crews%20of%20people%20for%20up%20to%2016%20months%20to%20conduct%20research%20on%20the%20frozen%20continent.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDuring%20the%20March%20to%20October%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bas.ac.uk%2F%5C%22%3Epolar%20winter%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20teams%20spend%20six%20months%20in%20near%20darkness%20%E2%80%93%20and%20from%20May%20to%20August%2C%20in%20complete%20darkness%20%E2%80%93%20facing%20outside%20temperatures%20of%20up%20to%20-60C%2C%20wind%20speeds%20of%20160%20km%2Fh%20(100%20mph)%20and%20storms%20which%20prevent%20almost%20all%20outdoor%20activity.%20Limited%20internet%20coverage%20can%20also%20prevent%20constant%20communication%20with%20the%20outside%20world.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20the%20last%20year%2C%20we%20have%20researched%20how%20life%20in%20Antarctica%20influences%20people's%20experience%20of%20time.%20Each%20month%2C%20we%20asked%20crew%20members%20how%20time%20felt%20like%20it%20was%20passing%20in%20comparison%20to%20before%20their%20mission.%20Trapped%20on%20base%2C%20with%20limited%20contact%20with%20the%20outside%20world%2C%20you%20might%20expect%20time%20to%20drag.%20However%2C%20our%20results%20suggest%20the%20opposite%20may%20be%20true.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnalysis%20of%20crew%20members'%20experiences%20indicated%20that%20being%20constantly%20busy%20with%20complex%20tasks%20such%20as%20scientific%20research%20helped%20time%20to%20pass%20swiftly%2C%20according%20to%2080%25%20of%20crew%20responses.%20Only%203%25%20of%20responses%20indicated%20that%20time%20actually%20dragged%2C%20and%20these%20reports%20occurred%20when%20nights%20were%20long%20and%20there%20was%20little%20to%20do.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThese%20experiences%20may%20provide%20hope%20for%20those%20stuck%20on%20the%20ISS.%20Like%20life%20on%20an%20Antarctic%20station%2C%20these%20Nasa%20astronauts%20have%20a%20busy%20and%20mentally%20demanding%20existence.%20These%20factors%20may%20help%20time%20to%20pass%20quickly.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20a%20key%20factor%20of%20their%20wait%20may%20be%20their%20ability%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fjournals.sagepub.com%2Fdoi%2F10.1177%2F2043808718778982%5C%22%3Etolerate%20the%20uncertainty%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20when%20they%20will%20return.%20Wilmore%20and%20Williams%20will%20spend%20their%20time%20in%20a%20space%20equivalent%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nasa.gov%2Finternational-space-station%2Fspace-station-facts-and-figures%2F%5C%22%3Einside%20a%20Boeing%20747%3C%2Fa%3E%20plane.%20But%20better%20information%20about%20%E2%80%9Cwhen%E2%80%9D%20things%20will%20happen%20and%20%E2%80%9Cwhy%E2%80%9D%20delays%20are%20being%20incurred%20can%20help%20people%20to%20tolerate%20waiting%20and%20reduce%20its%20impact%20on%20their%20wellbeing.%3Cimg%20referrerpolicy%3D%5C%22no-referrer-when-downgrade%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcounter.theconversation.com%2Fcontent%2F236546%2Fcount.gif%3Fdistributor%3Drepublish-lightbox-basic%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20Conversation%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cspan%3E(%3Cstrong%3EAuthors%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheconversation.com%2Fprofiles%2Fruth-ogden-1182467%5C%22%3ERuth%20Ogden%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Professor%20of%20the%20Psychology%20of%20Time%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheconversation.com%2Finstitutions%2Fliverpool-john-moores-university-1319%5C%22%3ELiverpool%20John%20Moores%20University%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheconversation.com%2Fprofiles%2Fdaniel-eduardo-vigo-1631723%5C%22%3EDaniel%20Eduardo%20Vigo%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Senior%20Researcher%20in%20Chronobiology%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheconversation.com%2Finstitutions%2Fpontificia-universidad-catolica-de-argentina-5531%5C%22%3EPontificia%20Universidad%20Cat%C3%B3lica%20de%20Argentina%3C%2Fa%3E)%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E(%3Cstrong%3EDisclosure%20Statement%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Ruth%20Ogden%20receives%20funding%20from%20The%20British%20Academy%2C%20The%20Wellcome%20Trust%2C%20the%20Economic%20and%20Social%20Research%20Council%2C%20CHANSE%20and%20Horizon%202020.%20This%20piece%20was%20written%20as%20part%20of%20the%20Wellcome%20Trust%20Project%20%26quot%3BAfter%20the%20End%26quot%3B%20225238%2FZ%2F22%2FZ.%20The%20work%20reported%20in%20this%20article%20is%20in%20collaboration%20with%20ESA%20and%20IIA%20as%20part%20of%20the%20SPACE-TIME%20project.%20Daniel%20Vigo%20is%20a%20research%20c