%3Cp%3EAsteroids%20have%20different%20chemical%20makeups%20depending%20on%20where%20they%20formed%20in%20our%20solar%20system.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20determine%20the%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Edino-killing%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Easteroid's%20origin%2C%20researchers%20examined%20the%20various%20elements%20in%20samples%20taken%20from%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eseveral%20locations%20dating%20to%20the%20time%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmass-extinction-earth-take-10-million-years-recover-2019-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emass%20extinction%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20particular%2C%20they%20looked%20at%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Foppenheimer-science-to-understand-physics-atomic-bombs-2023-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eelement%20ruthenium%3C%2Fa%3E.%20It's%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.rsc.org%2Fperiodic-table%2Felement%2F44%2Fruthenium%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erare%3C%2Fa%3E%20metal%20on%20Earth%20but%20is%20more%20abundant%20in%20asteroids.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERuthenium%20levels%20can%20be%20a%20good%20indicator%20of%20whether%20an%20asteroid%20%26quot%3Boriginally%20formed%20in%20the%20outer%20solar%20system%20or%20in%20the%20inner%20solar%20system%2C%26quot%3B%20Mario%20Fischer-G%C3%B6dde%2C%20one%20of%20the%20researchers%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFischer-G%C3%B6dde%20and%20his%20colleagues%20found%20that%2C%20unlike%20many%20other%20impactors%20over%20the%20last%20541%20million%20years%2C%20the%20Chicxulub%20impactor%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchicxulub-asteroid-strike-cretaceous-paleogene-extinction-2017-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ekilled%20the%20dinosaurs%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20up%20to%2075%25%20of%20all%20life%20on%20Earth%20formed%20in%20the%20outer%20%E2%80%94%20not%20the%20inner%20%E2%80%94%20solar%20system.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20the%20impactor%20